http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/business/Kotak-Mahindra-Bank-Q3-net-at-Rs-635-cr/article14005856.ece

Private sector lender Kotak Mahindra Bank on Monday reported a net profit of Rs 635 crore on a standalone basis for the quarter ended December 31 as compared to Rs 465 crore recorded during the same period the previous year.The numbers, however, are not exactly comparable as this quarter’s numbers included the merger of ING Vysya Bank, effective from April 1, 2015. The net interest income for the period under review was Rs 1,766 crore while net interest margin stood at 4.3 per cent.“Our Casa is at 35 per cent. We have seen growth in both current account and savings account deposits,” said Jaimin Bhatt, president and chief financial officer, Kotak Mahindra Bank. The deposit base of the bank stood at Rs 1.3 lakh crore. The gross non-performing assets ratio stood at 2.3 per cent as on end December while net NPA was 0.96 per cent. Provision was slightly higher than what the market was expecting, which came at Rs 235 crore as compared to Rs 30 crore in the year ago period.Provision impact“Provision impact, including provision on security receipts and credit substitutes, on Q3FY16 results was Rs 235 crore, of which a significant portion was from the erstwhile ING Vysya Bank,” the bank said.On the loan growth front, the lender said it was on track to achieve 15 per cent loan growth that was projected at the beginning of the year.